			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ahhh  The druids in WC.  I just recently camped them from 39-42 then they started conning light blue.  Here's what I did:<br><br>Summon your 39 fire pet.  To check the lvl just send it in on one of the low mobs that walk nearby.  DO NOT accept one that hits for less than 38.  Summon him 2 dagger of symbols and a full suit of fine plate.  Be patient and let the pet DS himself.  Check the names on both druids,  if one is Ceel Moonwhisper You want to send the pet in on him first because he will drive you insane because he will heal the other one.  To pull  just send the pet in and they will both aggro him.  Count to 5  then cast renew elements on your pet.  Once the renew gem has repopped heal him again.  Then click on each to see which one is lowest in health.  Cast blaze once and he should be going down.  Here's the key part,  let the pet finish tanking the other one till death if his health is around 40% or so just to split the spawn up a little.  <br><br>When the first one respawns IMMEDIATELY pull with malise to get him to come to you and out of the aggro range of the other.  Have a hot key set up to tell your pet to /pet back off so that he doesn't go to the spawn point When you get nuked.  Then just chain 2 blazes and he is usually running.  After that just send the pet in on the other.  You dont need to malise again except for the first respawn.<br><br>Why fire and not air?  The druids (or rangers) use a fire based nuke which does little dmg to the fire pet plus the DS is ESSENTIAL when pulling off breaking the spawn. The fire-based DD hits for 175 btw.<br><br>Please forgive the lenght as I just wanted no surprises for all my fellow mages )<br><br>Rufuz Bellylint<br>Mage of the 42nd Summoning<br>Karana Server<br>Proud member of Illuminatus <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rufuz>Rufuz</A> at: 2/26/02 12:02:32 pm<br></i></span><span class="gensmall">