			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually, it's fairly easy to break this camp.  The triick is to take the caster first, and use your bolt at 60% or less.  I just did 39-42 here.<br><br>Fire pet, BO2, lev rings, elemental defender, summoned armor and daggers.  Basically you want all of the AC and saves you can get.  With the new patch giving you your strongest pet, you're in good shape.<br><br>As you look north to the druid rings, the one on the left is the caster.  Send your pet in to him.  Make sure he stays on him -- I've had a couple cases where the pet has switched targets.<br><br>Watch the casters health.  When he dips into the 70% range, nuke with your bolt.  He should be walking at that point, and yor pet should be around half life.  Nuke him again, and he'll go down.  Heal your pet if you want and try to drag out the battle with the second one a bit so you have time to kill the 1st pop on the next spawn.  Nuke with your bolt when the druid is anywhere under 40% health and you'll drop him instantly.<br><br>After that, I park my pet on their spot and when the next pop happens (caster), I send him in instantly.  Malise and bolt at  60% or so and he's dead.  Then wait a minute or two to spread out the spawn a bit.<br><br>Once you've broken the spawn, this is an easy camp.  Your pet can solo either of them without your help.   And the loot is amazing... from 39-42 I made about 5.5kp. <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
