			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There are two ways to break this camp:<br><br>1)  watch with amusement as a lvl 11 DE necro ports in and then runs off and dies.  pull the druids as they walk back (since only one goes returns home at a time).<br><br>2)  Lvl 39 water pet (focus)-- plate, daggers of symbols x 2, ring of flight x 2, elemental defender.  cast expedience (probably not really necessary), BOII, Barrier of Combustion and send your pet in.  Make sure you attack the MALE druid first because he heals.  When is health is ~ 45% range nuke him with cinder bolt to finish him off.  Much lower than that and he will start to heal and you will start having to worry about your pet health.  Once he is dead, heal your pet and let him finish off the other druid.  Take your time, prolong the fight as long as possible..<br><br>Once the druid pops again...immediately pull him away from the rings.  I usually set up south of the rings and in this case I would nuke him and run over that hill (while keeping your pet at bay).  Eventually he should show up and then you can engage him and kill (see above tactics).  Wait a bit to break the spawn and then go kill the other druid.  Wash, rinse, repeat.<br><br>The experience is +/- 1% per kill (I'm using the new GUI-- I don't pay attention to blues per kill anymore).  In other words, exp isn't all that good but the loot is great.  You can easily clear anywhere from 5 plat (FS weapons) on up to 20 plat (FS weapons, bow, and gem or something) per kill.<br><br>Good luck. <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
