			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I killed the two druids that spawn in ec throughout 41 until 42 (they turn light blue at 42).  Basically I parked my pet (fire w/ plate, bracer,rings,daggers, burnout and expedience) a little ways from the camp and nuked one with cinderbolt from a distance to break the spawn. Usually what happened is that the druid would come running and I would send my pet in. Depending on how much damage I did with my nuke, my pet was usually able to keep him/her off of me. Using malaise works just as well for pulling and is generally safer, as landing a 369+ nuke tends to really irk them.   Once the first druid was dead, I would bring pet and myself closer, kill the other druid and then sit down to med. I think there was about 5 - 6 minute respawn time.<br><br>The only real difficulty I encountered in breaking the spawn was that sometimes the druid would not run over to me. I tried to malaise or nuke from a distance and run back a bit. The druid would stand there and cast on me, or, he/she would use a ranged weapon on me and my pet would go flying in to bonk them. Killing two at once is doable, but for me it usually got very messy =( <br><br>There are two types: druids and rangers. Both dropped fine steel weapons, chain armor and the occasional water/mead/beer. Coin drop was good too.  Spells cast consisted of ensnaring roots, creeping crud and lightning bolt(?). The most damage I took from them in one nuke was 174. However, melee is a whole other story, they can hit hard and fast - causing me to run in circles while my pet tries to get them off of me.  <br><br>The money was awesome. I made 500pp and went from 41 to 42. At 42 they conned light blue to me so I moved on =) <br>cheers and good luck!<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silinye>silinye</A> at: 12/21/02 2:56:32 am<br></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
