			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I broke the spawn using a Fire Pet and an Air Pet.  Cast Barrier of Combustion on Air.  The Air's stun is helpful but the Fire Pet's high fire resist is more beneficial.  Make sure you give your pet the set of Plate armor and two daggers.  Keep your eyes out for people playing Druids that take roleplaying seriously.  I had a level 46 Druid start healing them when I was trying to break the spawn.  Once the spawn is broken however it is so easy to hold them camp.  Summon some bags and sit back to rake in fine steel.  I suggest binding yourself to the zone line of EC.  If you are in trouble or if some high level person kills the merchant on the other side of the rings then you're only a button push away. <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
