			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Did these 2 last night with 39 focused air pet.  I used air so it could interrupt their casting.  I buffed the pet with BOII, Expedience, Barrier of Combustion and a full set of summoned plate.
<br />

<br />
Facing them from behind, I sent my pet on the one on the left.   This is the one that heals the other when fighting.   I casted Shock of Spikes, healed my pet once, then Blaze.  Boom dead druid.  Pet starts on the Ranger, I cast one more heal then Blaze then Shock of Spikes to finish it.  Use Blaze when they are around 1/2 health, that's when they will start to try and heal.
<br />

<br />
Never got touched in 90 minutes of fighting.  
<br />

<br />
These 2 have low hitpoints, you'll see their health bar move dramatically even when using Shock of Spikes.
<br />

<br />
Loot is amazing, almost 300pp in 90 minutes.  Best thing is you can sell to the vendor at the druid ring.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
